    "notes": "Phase 2 verification 2026-05-29 (Agent A). Radius/Teff/luminosity recommended switched from Rains 2020 to Boyajian 2012 (both CHARA-class interferometry, Boyajian has tighter fractional uncertainty: 0.45% vs 0.75% on R; 0.27% vs 0.59% on Teff; 0.8% vs 2.5% on L; method-tier tiebreak per add-star skill). 40 Eri A confirmed in both samples (Rains 2020 Table 1 as star #7 of 16 southern; Boyajian 2012 sample as GJ 166A). Documented Ma 2018 vs Bond 2017 age divergence: Ma 2018 isochrone 6.9 +/- 4.7 Gyr from K-dwarf SED+PARSEC isochrone fit, while Bond 2017 IFMR-derived system-coeval ~1.8 Gyr from 40 Eri B white-dwarf progenitor (initial mass ~1.8 M_sun, MS lifetime 1.7 Gyr + 122 Myr cooling). Bond 2017 explicitly says 'earlier concerns about an excessive age...appear to be resolved' (Section 6.2). Phase 3 synthesis adopts ~1.8 Gyr in Decisions but documents both in Canonical alternatives. Ma 2018 [Fe/H] is -0.42 +/- 0.04 (not -0.29; that came from Diaz 2018); Ma 2018 alt added. Burrows 2024 reports rotation period as '~42 days' with no formal uncertainty stated in the paper - earlier DB had a fabricated +/-2.5 d; replaced with paper-stated value and no uncertainty key. Pre-Burrows P_rot literature is contradictory: Saar & Osten 1997 cite ~37-38 d, Diaz 2018 sees ~38 d in HARPS S-indices, and Burrows 2024 NEID activity analysis lands at ~42 d. Planet HD 26965 b (Ma 2018 'Vulcan') refuted by Burrows 2024 multi-instrument 16-year RV; not in planets_curated.json. No 2025/2026 post-Burrows confirmation or replacement candidate found."
  },
